produces mineralocorticoids","The tissue originates from neuroectoderm","The zona reticularis produces glucocorticoids","The zona fasciculata produces androgens","The cortex consists of two distinct zones"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe adrenal cortex develops from mesoderm and consists of three distinct zones, each producing different steroid hormones:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe zona glomerulosa\u003C/strong\u003E is the outermost layer that produces mineralocorticoids (primarily aldosterone)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe tissue\u003C/strong\u003E is derived from mesoderm, while the adrenal medulla originates from neuroectoderm\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe zona reticularis\u003C/strong\u003E produces androgens, not glucocorticoids\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe zona fasciculata\u003C/strong\u003E produces glucocorticoids (primarily cortisol), not androgens\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EThere are \u003Cstrong\u003Ethree distinct zones\u003C/strong\u003E, not two\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The adrenal cortex develops from mesoderm and produces three classes of steroid hormones: mineralocorticoids, glucocorticoids, and androgens","The adrenal cortex consists of three distinct zones: zona glomerulosa (mineralocorticoids), zona fasciculata (glucocorticoids), and zona reticularis (androgens)"],"references":["Lotfi CFP, Kremer JL, Dos Santos Passaia B, Cavalcante IP. The human adrenal cortex: growth control and disorders. Clinics (Sao Paulo). 2018 Sep 6;73(suppl 1):e473s. doi: 10.6061/clinics/2018/e473s. PMID: 30208164; PMCID: PMC6113920.","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016).